column2: Pollen floating on water- hazy- hot- windy.  Memorial day - heavier than usual traffic.  Five boats (usually three tops).
Wind 10-15 mph from SW 3 boats on lake.  Partly cloudy- rained yesterday.
Partly cloudy + calm.  Rain last night.  Three boats on lake.  Lake temp.  78 degrees @ 13'.
Partly cloudy- windy- 2 boats on lake.
Rain all day yesterday and part of day before.  Sun/partly cloudy.
Much rain this week.  Lake up 2 or 3'.  Coot on lake.  Sun - no wind.
Ice off- breezy (1 goose nest)- 9 Canadian geese- 2 loons- 2 wood- 2 mallard.
Oak pollen ( ) on lake.  80 degrees- loon pair on lake.
Following 3 days of rain- level was very high.  Lake level: very high
Lowest water since 1993.  Bright sun- cold- clear water.
Another significant rain. Lake now over 9" above
Particles suspended in water. Water exceptionally

column1: high. Water running from Snake Lake into Two Island Lake since early September.

column2: Rare strand of utricularia. Water 2 feet above normal.
Water continues very high - 2' above average.
Level dropped 6" after long dry spell.
Pollen film on surface in bays and suspended in water.  Loon on nest
One loon chick (out of 2 hatched on Memorial Day) doing well. Surface temp was 86 deg two days ago- today is 80.
Loon and chick confronting us--very vocal
Loon on nest NE side of island
Loon chicks (2) hatched and doing well. Calico pennants (very red)- flying tandem + dipping.
Utricularia fragments. A few calico pennants flying solo; 2 green darners; 1 widow skimmer.
Utricularia fragments. Loon is curious (+ calling). Still 2 young and 2 adults. Great blue heron. Recent heavy rains (2 wks) raised level 3-4 in. Clear blue sky.
Utricularia low. 2 young loons + 1 adult fishing. Grey treefrogs calling. Great blue heron on island. Sunny- wind lt.
this follows high winds- snow- lows in mid 20's.
Lt breeze- sun; pollen- "cotton" on lake
Breezy; hundreds of calico pennants flying tandem
Loons with 1 day-old chick- on the back and on the water. Second egg abandoned.
Two sandhills fly over- calling. Loon chick alone on lake. Scattered calico pennants.
1 adult with 1 young loon; 2 green-backed herons; water at depression-era low; 2.5" rain in past week. Bracken fern turning brown. Virtually no utricularia.
Goose nesting on tiny island; Loon nest with two eggs on SE side of main island; another goose nesting on "third island".
Loon on NEW nest on NW side main island. Eagle soaring- bullfrog calling- chalk-fronted corporals- white water lilies flowering. New house being built.

Bullfrogs + green frogs calling- hundreds of calico pennants dipping in tandem- 2 widow skimmers- painted turtles- water striders first appearing in large numbers- 2 loons- large bloom of white water lilies blooming. 1" heavy rain last night.
Calico pennants dipping- 2 loons- white water lilies in flower. 1.25" rain 48 hrs ago.
Two loons swimming; Canada goos sitting on nest on tiny island. Clear.
Clear. Pollen on lake. Two loons swimming; two canada geese families fledged. (New temp battery)
Bullfrogs calling; calico pennants dipping; widow skimmers at island shoreline; newly-hatched rough-winged swallows being fed at pine snag on island; snapping turtle under boat. Clear.
1 loon-- dragonfly. Partly cloudy. Very low water level.
Strong winds past 3 days dropped water surface temp from 69 to 63.
Kingfisher; white waterlillies blooming; green darner; calico pennant dipping.
Water level up 4" (significant rain in past 2 weeks). Partly cloudy- breezy; waterlillies.
1 goose nesting; loon pair on lake; high thin clouds
lots of pollen; loon nest raided yesterday; sunny- calm; chalk-fronted corporals- damsel present.
2 loons on lake; calico pennants dipping; dot tail whiteface landed on boat; common green darner.
Twelve-spotted skimmer (1 male)- several calico pennant males; lots of white water lilies in bloom; large group of geese; loon; copious rainfall in past week- including last night.
2 anglers; meadowhawk; white waterlillies still flowering; calm- sunny
several small red meadow hawks flying tandem on lake
beaver swimming; 2 pair canada geese; installed wood duck house on island; loon arrived on lake at 3:30 PM
breezy- hazy bright; 2 geese and 2 loons on lake
Pair of loons- on nest on island. Dragonflies: many chalk-fronted corporal and calico pennant- a green darner- a twelve-spotted skimmer
Bluets in tandem; calico pennants flying; 2 loons on lake- nest empty. Scuba diver and snorkeler on lake. Lake is higher due to significant rain in past week.

Calico pennants flying over the lake (6-12 ). A mouse appeared in the boat- jumped out- and swam to shore. A few masses of utricularia. A pontoon appeared at the landing- surveyed the scene- and drove away.
Clear sky; no loons; 9 canada geese; water very clear and very low.
Lake level is at or near all-time low.
2 loons- 8 geese- 1 mallard. Lake level up 6" from last fall- but still very low.

2 loons with 2 chicks- hatched 6/14/2013. Bullfrog calling; calico pennants in tandem; american emerald- dusky club tail- common green darner- common baskettail- bluet- chalk-fronted corporal. Iris and white waterlillies blooming.
Common green darner- twelve-spotted skimmer- calico pennant. Adult loon- osprey. White water lillies flowering.
Loon- adult + chick; meadow hawks- common green darner
Bald eagle. Pairs of sympetrum flying tandem.
Loon pair- one on nest on tiny island. Green darner pair flying together. Suspended pollen in water.

Two loons with a chick on the back (first seen 6/15). Twelve-spotted skimmers numerous around island. Frosted whitefaces numerous- chalk-fronted corporals numerous and dipping- hagens bluet pair in cop- common green darner- 1 calico pennant- dusky club tails.
Two loons with month-old chick. Calico peanuts dipping- dot-tailed whitefaces. Green- leopard- and bullfrogs.
Young loon still present- adults come and go.

Great color on trees. No loons. Some algae rising near surface near shore. An unusual amount of individual large-leafed pondweed plants and lilies breaking the surface scattered around the lake in deeper water. Odes seen for the first time: spotted spreadings (numerous- in long grasses in the protected bays)- whiteface meadowhawks- and a mosaic darner (species?)
Very quiet- leaves mostly down- large rafts of leaves floating in north shore bays.
Loon- great blue heron- one goose nest each on big island and small island. Water continuing to rise slowly.
2 loons- nesting on tiny island; pair of anax junius in tandem; common basket tail teneral; damselflies; mallard flying; 3 geese on water; western painted turtles sunning. Water level is very high.
Loons: adult pair plus juvenile; swamp spreadings flying tandem; ajax junius; 3 boats; harebell along shore blooming; pickerel weed + white water lilies flowering; water 2.05- very high; wind WNW 4.
Lake extremely high. Mallard pair- loon- canada goose pair. Paired green darner.
Lots of calico pennants dipping; twelve spotted skimmer; chalk-fronted corporal; anax junius flying in tandem.

column1: Loon on nest on island (SE corner) and second loon present on lake.

column2: Anax junius in tandem- calico peanuts dipping- widow skimmers abundant around islands; 2 twelve spotted skimmers; unspecified whitefaces.

column1: 2 adult loons- egg shells near nest
Pair of Canada geese. Could not locate a loon nest this year. One located goose nest is completed. Water is extraordinarily high.

column2: 1 loon fishing near island. 3 turkey vultures circling.

column1: Many dragonflies: chalk fronted corporal- calico pennant- green darner

column2: Calm- sun; a few likely calico pennants; bluets;
Pileated woodpecker. No odes- loons- or people.
3? rain 2 days ago; maples turning red
